Classification in the consolidated financial statements
The pre-tax charges for each year are shown within operating profit in a separate line item on the consolidated statements of
income. In the consolidated balance sheets, reductions in assets are recorded against the carrying value of the related assets and
unpaid amounts are recorded as other current or long-term liabilities (see Note 7). On the consolidated statements of cash flows, the
pre-tax impact of these charges, net of cash payments, is shown as an adjustment to reconcile net income to net cash provided by
operating activities. In Note 18 Segment Information, Linde excluded these charges from its management definition of segment
operating profit; a reconciliation of segment operating profit to consolidated operating profit is shown within the segment operating
profit table.
