Linde performs its goodwill impairment tests annually as of October 1 or more frequently if events or circumstances indicate that
an impairment loss may have been incurred. For the fourth quarter 2022 test, the company applied the FASB's accounting guidance
which allows the company to first assess qualitative factors to determine the extent of additional quantitative analysis, if any, that
may be required to test goodwill for impairment. Based on the qualitative assessments performed, the company concluded that it
was more likely than not that the fair value of each reporting unit substantially exceeded its carrying value and therefore, further
quantitative analysis was not required. As a result, no impairment was recorded. There were no indicators of impairment since the
annual goodwill impairment test was performed through December 31, 2022.
